node.text:
“A partnership to bring hope to a nation through sport.”

Together, with Mission of Hope, we are proud to announce that both phase one and two of the Haiti Sports Complex have been completed!

This facility includes an 18,000 sq. foot multipurpose building and a full-size turf soccer field in Titanyen, Haiti.

The sports complex will serve more than 15,000 children every year, and by keeping the hope we all have in Jesus at the center everything we do, it will be a symbol for generations to come. 

@ao1foundation 
@mohhaiti 

#AO1 #HaitiSportsComplex

node.text:
Words will never be enough, but we are forever grateful 🙏🏻

・・・
The freedom that we walk in everyday is a gift because of the brave men and women that have given their lives defending it.

Let us not forget the sacrifice, pain, heartbreak, loneliness and helplessness of those families who have lost a loved one fighting for our freedom.

Today and everyday, we thank you.

"The Lord bless you and keep you; The Lord make his face shine upon you and be gracious to you; The Lord turn his face towards you and give you peace."
